If we say that Path was obligated to return the item at all, then we open all item awards up to second thinking.<br>
<br>
When i am on a raid and an item i want is awarded to another, thats all there is to it.. if the process doesnt work that way, then everyone would be entitled to lobby the raid leader to take the item back and give it to them..<br>
<br>
Not only does the item belong to Pathological, rightfully and morally, but returning it would set a bad precedent.. W<br>
<br>
Whatever his motivation, keeping the item was the right thing to do..<br>
<br>
Of course, had this been a guild raid, that would be different..   <br>
<br>
